---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro"
import DeckingCalc from "../../../components/calculators/DeckingCalc"
import EstimateMethodology from "../../../components/EstimateMethodology.astro"
import { graphSchema, webApplicationSchema, faqPageSchema, howToSchema, mathSolverSchema, breadcrumbListSchema } from "../../../lib/schema"
import RelatedCalculators from "../../../components/ui/RelatedCalculators.astro"

const canonical = "https://homeplanninghub.com/calculators/decking/";
const title = "Decking Calculator";
const description = "Calculate how many deck boards you need. Enter deck dimensions and board size to get board count, linear feet, square footage, and fastener estimates.";
const formula = "Boards = Ceil((Deck Width (ft) x 12) / (Board Width (in) + Gap (in))) | Linear Ft = Boards x Deck Length";
const PAGE_PATH = canonical.replace("https://homeplanninghub.com", "");

const schema = graphSchema(
  breadcrumbListSchema([
    { name: "Home", path: "/" },
    { name: "Specialty", path: "/calculators/" },
    { name: title, path: PAGE_PATH },
  ]),
  webApplicationSchema(title, description, canonical),
  mathSolverSchema({ name: title, description, formula, url: canonical }),
  howToSchema(title, description, [
    { name: "Measure area", text: "Review your project measurements." },
    { name: "Enter dimensions", text: "Input your project dimensions into the calculator." },
    { name: "Get estimate", text: "Review your material estimate and adjust as needed." },
  ]),
  faqPageSchema([
    { q: "How many deck boards for a 12x12 deck?", a: "For a 12x12 deck using 5.5\" boards with 1/8\" gap: (144/5.625) = 26 boards. Add 10% waste = 29 boards." },
    { q: "What gap should I leave between deck boards?", a: "1/8\" for treated lumber, 1/4\" for hardwood. Treated lumber shrinks as it dries, so gaps will widen over time." },
    { q: "How many fasteners per deck board?", a: "Two fasteners at each joist intersection. For 16\" OC joists on a 12 ft board, that's about 18 fasteners per board." },
  ], canonical)
);
---
<Layout title={title} description={description} schema={schema}>
<article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-6 py-4">
  <nav class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-[var(--fg-muted)] mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <a href="/" class="hover:text-[var(--fg)] transition-colors">Home</a>
    <svg class="w-3 h-3" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"/></svg>
    <a href="/calculators/" class="hover:text-[var(--fg)] transition-colors">Calculators</a>
    <svg class="w-3 h-3" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"/></svg>
    <span class="text-[var(--fg-secondary)] font-medium">Decking Calculator</span>
  </nav>
  <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-balance">Decking Calculator</h1>
  <p class="text-base text-[var(--fg-secondary)] text-pretty max-w-2xl">Calculate how many deck boards you need. Enter deck dimensions and board size to get board count, linear feet, square footage, and fastener estimates.</p>

  <section><DeckingCalc client:visible /></section>
  <EstimateMethodology formula={formula} assumptions={["Standard 5/4\" decking or 2x6 boards.", "Board gaps of 1/8\" between boards.", "10% waste factor recommended for cuts and mistakes."]} />

  <section>
    <h2 id="how-to-calculate" class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">How to Calculate Deck Board Quantity</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-4 text-pretty">
      Calculating the number of deck boards needed depends on three factors: deck width, board width, and the gap between boards. The process is straightforward but requires attention to the joint gap and waste factor.
    </p>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 flex flex-col gap-3 text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)]">
      <li><strong>Convert deck width to inches:</strong> Multiply the deck width in feet by 12 to get inches.
        <div class="my-2 p-3 bg-[var(--bg-muted)] rounded-lg font-mono text-center text-xs">Width (in) = Width (ft) &times; 12</div>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Calculate board + gap width:</strong> Add the board width and the gap width together.
        <div class="my-2 p-3 bg-[var(--bg-muted)] rounded-lg font-mono text-center text-xs">Effective Width = Board Width (in) + Gap (in)</div>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Divide to find board count:</strong> Divide the total deck width in inches by the effective width and round up.
        <div class="my-2 p-3 bg-[var(--bg-muted)] rounded-lg font-mono text-center text-xs">Boards = &lceil;Width (in) &divide; Effective Width&lceil;</div>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Calculate linear feet:</strong> Multiply the board count by the deck length to get total linear feet of decking material needed.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="example" class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">Example Deck Calculation</h2>
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--card-bg)] p-4">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--fg)] mb-2">12&prime; &times; 12&prime; deck with 5.5-inch boards and 1/8-inch gap</p>
      <ul class="flex flex-col gap-1.5 text-xs text-[var(--fg-secondary)]">
        <li><strong>Deck width:</strong> 12 ft &times; 12 = <strong>144 inches</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Effective board width:</strong> 5.5 in + 0.125 in = <strong>5.625 in</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Boards needed:</strong> 144 &divide; 5.625 = <strong>26 boards</strong></li>
        <li><strong>With 10% waste:</strong> 26 &times; 1.10 = <strong>29 boards</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Linear feet:</strong> 29 boards &times; 12 ft = <strong>348 linear feet</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Fasteners:</strong> 29 &times; 18 screws per board = <strong>522 screws</strong></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>


  <section>
    <h2 id="common-mistakes" class="text-xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">Common Mistakes in Decking Estimation</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--card-bg)] p-4">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--fg)] mb-1">Forgetting the gap between boards</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-[var(--fg-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-pretty">Deck boards need gaps for drainage and expansion. Treated lumber needs 1/8 inch gaps; hardwood needs 1/4 inch. Failing to account for the gap results in ordering too few boards and installing them too tight, which traps moisture and causes cupping.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--card-bg)] p-4">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--fg)] mb-1">Ignoring board shrinkage</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-[var(--fg-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-pretty">Pressure-treated lumber is often installed wet and shrinks as it dries. A 5.5-inch board can shrink to 5.25 inches over time. This creates wider gaps than expected. Account for this by not overspacing during installation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--card-bg)] p-4">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--fg)] mb-1">Not planning diagonal layouts</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-[var(--fg-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-pretty">Diagonal decking requires significantly more material — typically 15-20% more than straight-laid boards. The mitered ends at the perimeter also increase waste. Adjust your waste factor to 15% for diagonal patterns.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 id="faq" class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
      <details class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--card-bg)] p-4"><summary class="text-sm font-semibold cursor-pointer"><h3 class="text-sm font-semibold m-0">How many deck boards for a 12x12 deck?</h3></summary><p class="mt-3 text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)]">For a 12x12 deck using 5.5" boards with 1/8" gap: (144/5.625) = 26 boards. Add 10% waste = 29 boards.</p></details>
      <details class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--card-bg)] p-4"><summary class="text-sm font-semibold cursor-pointer"><h3 class="text-sm font-semibold m-0">What gap should I leave between deck boards?</h3></summary><p class="mt-3 text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)]">1/8" for treated lumber, 1/4" for hardwood. Treated lumber shrinks as it dries, so gaps will widen over time.</p></details>
      <details class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--card-bg)] p-4"><summary class="text-sm font-semibold cursor-pointer"><h3 class="text-sm font-semibold m-0">How many fasteners per deck board?</h3></summary><p class="mt-3 text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)]">Two fasteners at each joist intersection. For 16" OC joists on a 12 ft board, that's about 18 fasteners per board.</p></details>
    </div>
  </section>
  <RelatedCalculators slug="decking" />
</article>
</Layout>
